  "event_preview": "Circuit de Spa-Francorchamps is a 7.004 km (4.352 mi) permanent road course in the Ardennes forest in Stavelot, Belgium. The 2026 FIA Formula Regional European Championship third round takes place May 29–31 with two qualifying sessions and three races. Friday is reserved for collective testing.\n\nSebastian Wheldon leads the championship by 12 points over Reno Francot after winning twice at Zandvoort. Alexandre Munoz of ART Grand Prix has been competitive throughout the opening rounds and will look to challenge Wheldon. Alex Ninovic, Dion Gowda and Marcus Sæter have all shown strong pace. The second-generation Tatuus T-326 machinery continues to produce close racing across the field.",
